Bradford, 21, was legally armed and brandishing his gun reportedly to save lives in the mall shooting that was started by someone else.
A Hoover police officer shot Bradford on sight, apparently because of implicit racial bias.
It was immediately announced that Bradford was the mall shooter, as officials dragged his good name through the mud.
Meanwhile, authorities continued refusing to identify the officer involved in the shooting or release video of the incident.